However, it is worth noting that MNEs from the United States (US) have remained dominant in generating FDI outflows on a home-country basis (UNCTAD, 2015), which is also reflected in the number of research studies that draw on U.S. -based MNE-FDI data. Furthermore, the US, China, and Japan have been most often studied in the context of outward MNE FDI (see
Table 2
). The reasons for this might lie in (a) the magnitude of outward MNE FDI from these three countries and/or (b) the fact that data from these countries are more easily obtainable and that they thus provide better opportunities for quantitative analyses. Only a handful of studies have so far examined outward MNE-FDI from other countries such as India, Turkey, etc. (e.g., Bhaumik and Driffield, 2011, Narayanan and Bhat, 2011, Demirbag et al., 2009).
